# _headers — Civil Engineering Suite (Cloudflare Pages)
# Security headers for static files (images, CSS, etc.)
# Headers for encrypted pages are set directly in functions/[[path]].js
# NOTE: These headers apply ONLY to static assets — NOT to Pages Function responses.
#       Confirmed by Cloudflare official docs:
#       "Custom headers defined in the _headers file are not applied to responses
#        generated by Pages Functions, even if the request URL matches a rule."
#       All security headers for function routes (/, /footing-pro/, etc.) are
#       applied programmatically inside functions/[[path]].js via SHARED_SECURITY_HEADERS.
#
# FIX LOG (2026-04-14):
# [F1] Added /public/* block: X-Robots-Tag + Cache-Control + Content-Disposition
#      → Prevents Google from indexing encrypted .enc files. Without this,
#        Googlebot could crawl /public/pc_suite.enc and waste crawl budget.
# [F2] Added Cache-Control to /* catch-all for static HTML sub-app pages
#      (beam-pro/index.html, column-pro/index.html, etc.)
#
# FIX LOG (2026-04-17): PAYMENT GATEWAY INTEGRATION
# [P1] Added /payment/* block:
#      → Overrides CSP to allow Paymob SDK (accept.paymob.com) for script, connect, frame
#      → Overrides Permissions-Policy to REMOVE payment=() which blocks the payment API
#      → Sets Cache-Control: no-store (payment pages must never be cached)
#      → Sets X-Robots-Tag: noindex (payment pages must not be indexed)
# [P2] NOTE: /api/payment/* routes are Cloudflare Pages Functions — they do NOT
#      inherit _headers rules. Security headers are applied inside each function file.
#      Cloudflare `_headers` rules: later (more-specific) path rules override
#      earlier (less-specific) rules for duplicate headers on the same response.
#
# FIX LOG (2026-04-25):
# [H1] SYNTAX FIX: Removed inline comment (  # [F2] Default cache...) from inside
#      the /* block. Cloudflare Pages _headers does not define support for indented
#      comments within header blocks. An indented line starting with # is not a valid
#      header name:value pair — the parser behavior is undefined. The comment was
#      moved to the file header above. Cache-Control line is unchanged; it now
#      immediately follows the last header directive with no intervening comment.
# [H2] DEAD CODE REMOVAL: Removed /sitemap.xml block. The functions/[[path]].js
#      handler intercepts /sitemap.xml before static file serving and returns a
#      clean response directly. Cloudflare Pages confirms _headers NEVER applies
#      to Function responses. This block had zero effect on any actual sitemap
#      response — it was not setting any headers on the URL Googlebot fetches.
#      Removing it eliminates false confidence and parser ambiguity.

# [F2] Default cache for static HTML pages (sub-apps: beam-pro/index.html etc.)
/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload
  X-DNS-Prefetch-Control: off
  X-Permitted-Cross-Domain-Policies: none
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: unsafe-none
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: same-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), payment=(), accelerometer=(), gyroscope=(), magnetometer=(), display-capture=(), screen-wake-lock=(), autoplay=(), clipboard-read=()
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=600, must-revalidate

# [F1] FIX: Block crawlers from indexing encrypted .enc source files
/public/*
  X-Robots-Tag: noindex, noarchive, nosnippet
  Cache-Control: no-store
  Content-Disposition: attachment

/404.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=60

/404.css
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
  Content-Type: text/css; charset=utf-8

# NOTE: /sitemap.xml block intentionally absent — handled exclusively by
# functions/[[path]].js which returns only Content-Type + Cache-Control.
# _headers never applies to Function responses (Cloudflare Pages official docs).

/robots.txt
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400
  Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8

/manifest.json
  Content-Type: application/manifest+json; charset=utf-8
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *

/fonts/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: cross-origin
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *

/images/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
  Cross-Origin-Resource-Policy: cross-origin

/footing-pro/images/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
